        for something I&#x27;d feel passionate about. I tried many different areas, in vain. I didn’t feel happy, I
        missed the enthusiasm, the ’aha’ reaction, which made me feel that yes, this was my dream job! I was looking
        for the right profession until 2005, when first went to a massage that changed my life forever.</p>
      <p>It helped me to release my everyday problems and made me feel relaxed and disconnected. On that day I knew
        for certain I would be a masseuse! My goal is to help others, give the opportunity to break the stressed days
        and create unique atmosphere where everybody could concentrate for physical and spiritual replenishment.</p>
      <p>In 2005 I came up with the idea that besides my work I began to learn various types of massage. I have always
        striven for internal and external harmony so I started to learn the eastern and western massage types such as:
      </p>
      <ul role="list">
